<p1>Mechanics
<br>
<br>
Spotting - Tanks have a spotting range, which is the range in which they can spot. Factors affect spotting, such as the camo rating of the tank along with if they are hiding behind a bush or tree. 
<br>
<br>
Armor - Armor is a big thing in world of tanks as it can prevent you from taking damage. Either a tank can non-pen the armor or just bounce off. On top of this if the armor is angled, it increases the amount of armor you have. This is known as angling and makes a big difference in the amount of armor you have. Below are some diagrams of how it works. The left side picture is a picture of sidescraping which is a type of angling. The right side image is normal angling.
